00:38:28,221 --> 00:38:31,024
Teens should use
the smartwheel and--

00:38:31,024 --> 00:38:31,891
I'm not convinced. I'm out.

00:38:37,097 --> 00:38:38,698
(Kevin)
Here's my take on this--

00:38:38,698 --> 00:38:39,899
You've achieved a whole lot,

00:38:39,899 --> 00:38:42,435
putting this
whole thing together.

00:38:42,435 --> 00:38:44,904
You've taken an idea and gone
all the way to the White House.

00:38:44,904 --> 00:38:46,573
That's cool.

00:38:46,573 --> 00:38:48,775
Now if you only had
a good idea,

00:38:48,775 --> 00:38:49,976
just think
what you'd be doing.

00:38:52,312 --> 00:38:53,646
You will one day come up
with a good product

00:38:53,646 --> 00:38:56,583
that I can invest in,
and when that day comes,

00:38:56,583 --> 00:38:58,618
you're invited
back through those doors,

00:38:58,618 --> 00:39:02,422
and I will write you a check.
But today, no. I'm out.

00:39:02,422 --> 00:39:05,959
♪♪

00:39:11,364 --> 00:39:13,032
Three sharks are out.

00:39:13,032 --> 00:39:16,503
To get a deal,
the inventioneers need an offer

00:39:16,503 --> 00:39:18,171
from Robert or Mark.

00:39:18,171 --> 00:39:19,305
(Robert)
Here's where I'm at--

00:39:19,305 --> 00:39:20,774
I love cars, I race cars,

00:39:20,774 --> 00:39:22,776
I know
all the car company guys,

00:39:22,776 --> 00:39:25,311
and most importantly,

00:39:25,311 --> 00:39:28,047
I have a 16-year-old daughter
who just started to drive.

00:39:28,047 --> 00:39:30,116
I can't believe
this isn't an option

00:39:30,116 --> 00:39:32,118
within an existing car.

00:39:32,118 --> 00:39:34,220
Where I'm struggling
a little bit is,

00:39:34,220 --> 00:39:36,890
I think you're missing
the business that you're in.

00:39:36,890 --> 00:39:38,558
You think you're
in the smartwheel business,

00:39:38,558 --> 00:39:42,162
But the name of your company
or of you guys

00:39:42,162 --> 00:39:44,564
is the inventioneers.

00:39:44,564 --> 00:39:48,435
The smartwheel is simply
a product that you've invented.

00:39:48,435 --> 00:39:50,170
The thing to do
with a great invention

00:39:50,170 --> 00:39:52,906
is now go and sell it
to somebody.

00:39:52,906 --> 00:39:56,643
I think trying to manufacture it
and doing all this other stuff

00:39:56,643 --> 00:39:57,911
is just crazy.

00:40:01,381 --> 00:40:04,384
We did get, uh, another offer
to do a pilot study.

00:40:04,384 --> 00:40:05,351
We were actually able to talk

00:40:05,351 --> 00:40:07,754
with the U.S. Secretary
of Transportation Ray Lahood.

00:40:07,754 --> 00:40:09,956
He not only endorsed
the smartwheel,

00:40:09,956 --> 00:40:11,624
but he also offered
to set us up

00:40:11,624 --> 00:40:12,826
for a pilot study
on Mass transit vehicles.

00:40:15,161 --> 00:40:17,163
So what was the follow-up
to that?

00:40:17,163 --> 00:40:18,565
The follow-up is,

00:40:18,565 --> 00:40:20,633
we need more smartwheels
to test it with.

00:40:20,633 --> 00:40:24,170
(Robert) Here's what
I'm willing to do.

00:40:27,106 --> 00:40:30,577
I'll give you the $100,000
for 30%...

00:40:32,512 --> 00:40:34,447
contingent on

00:40:34,447 --> 00:40:36,316
taking it to a car company

00:40:36,316 --> 00:40:38,818
and them being interested
in moving forward

00:40:38,818 --> 00:40:41,020
with a licensing deal.

00:40:43,756 --> 00:40:46,025
Was anyone willing
to go in on that deal?

00:40:47,360 --> 00:40:49,028
What am I,
chopped liver to you?

00:40:49,028 --> 00:40:50,029
No, you are awesome.
My offer's not good enough?

00:40:50,029 --> 00:40:53,032
We are--we are on the edge
of our seats here.

00:40:53,032 --> 00:40:54,701
Robert,
I'll go in with you 50/50

00:40:54,701 --> 00:40:58,371
if you take out the contingency
on the car companies,

00:40:58,371 --> 00:41:00,707
because I think once we go
visit the car companies,

00:41:00,707 --> 00:41:03,309
and we've talked to them
not just about

00:41:03,309 --> 00:41:05,044
driver training for kids

00:41:05,044 --> 00:41:07,514
but also
the commercial applications,

00:41:07,514 --> 00:41:09,516
we have the opportunity
to pivot.

00:41:09,516 --> 00:41:11,918
My only issue is,
T.J.'s vision is to take...

00:41:11,918 --> 00:41:14,287
I agree. I-I agree.
The entire $100,000
to manufacture.

00:41:14,287 --> 00:41:15,154
I don't want to do that.

00:41:15,154 --> 00:41:16,756
No, I--Okay, so, T.J.,
would you be open to,

00:41:16,756 --> 00:41:19,025
once we discuss everything...
Mm-hmm.

00:41:19,025 --> 00:41:22,095
If the best course of action
is not necessarily

00:41:22,095 --> 00:41:24,097
to take that further along

00:41:24,097 --> 00:41:27,367
But talk to the car companies,
let them help us design it

00:41:27,367 --> 00:41:28,434
so we don't have to spend
all that money,

00:41:28,434 --> 00:41:30,436
so we have
a little dry powder left

00:41:30,436 --> 00:41:31,571
to--to evolve and pivot?

00:41:31,571 --> 00:41:33,373
Yeah.

00:41:33,373 --> 00:41:39,178
All right, Mark and I
will give you $100,000 for 30%.

00:41:39,178 --> 00:41:40,513
What do you say?

00:41:40,513 --> 00:41:42,382
No contingency?

00:41:42,382 --> 00:41:43,583
No contingency.

00:41:45,018 --> 00:41:47,086
That's a deal.

00:41:47,086 --> 00:41:49,489
(laughs)
All right.

00:41:49,489 --> 00:41:50,738
Thank you so much, guys.
Wow. Great job.

00:41:50,738 --> 00:41:52,371
Congratulations, guys.
Thank you.

00:41:52,371 --> 00:41:53,706
Thanks. Congratulations.
Nice to meet you.
Nice to meet you.

00:41:53,706 --> 00:41:55,441
(Robert) I love cars.
This is so cool.

00:41:55,441 --> 00:41:56,776
Here.

00:41:56,776 --> 00:41:58,511
(imitates engine revving)

00:41:58,511 --> 00:41:59,445
(inventioneers laugh)

00:42:02,515 --> 00:42:03,850
(laughs) We did it.

00:42:03,850 --> 00:42:04,304
(singsongy)
Oh, yeah. Oh, yeah.

00:42:04,304 --> 00:42:05,604
Oh, my gosh.

00:42:05,604 --> 00:42:06,504
We're investing
in these kids.

00:42:06,504 --> 00:42:08,372
They're super smart.
I--they are. They are.

00:42:08,372 --> 00:42:09,707
They're gonna do smart things.
They are gonna figure it out.

00:42:09,707 --> 00:42:10,641
I agree with you.
They're fantastic.

00:42:10,641 --> 00:42:14,245
But I have to also tell you,
I love the product.

00:42:14,245 --> 00:42:15,580
Jaiden's crying.

00:42:15,580 --> 00:42:16,914
(all laugh)

00:42:16,914 --> 00:42:18,282
It's okay. It's okay.

00:42:18,282 --> 00:42:19,617
(T.J.) Oh, wow.

00:42:19,617 --> 00:42:20,952
(girl) Oh, my goodness.

00:42:20,952 --> 00:42:22,420
I can't believe
that actually happened.

00:42:22,420 --> 00:42:23,421
(Jaiden, voice breaking)
The sharks actually

00:42:23,421 --> 00:42:25,222
treated us like adults,
and they valued our ideas.

00:42:25,222 --> 00:42:27,224
And it's great to see
someone else

00:42:27,224 --> 00:42:29,160
appreciate the smartwheel
as much as we do.

00:42:29,160 --> 00:42:31,162
(all) The inventioneers!

00:42:31,162 --> 00:42:34,098
(cheering)

